#: description: - - - - - - - - Overview of HEPData Record - - - - - - - -

Lower mass requirement for signal regions.
  • Gluinos and squarks
  • Staus and charginos
Discovery regions:
  • Yields
  • p0-values and limits
Signal yield tables:
  • MS-agnostic R-hadron search
  • Full-detector R-hadron search
  • MS-agnostic search for metastable gluino R-hadrons
  • Full-detector direct-stau search
  • Full-detector chargino search
Limits:
  • Gluino R-hadron search
  • Sbottom R-hadron search
  • Stop R-hadron search
  • Stau search
  • Chargino search
  • Meta-stable gluino R-hadron search
  • Meta-stable gluino R-hadron search
Acceptance and efficiency:
  • MS-agnostic R-hadron search
Truth quantities:
  • Flavor composition of 800 GeV stop R-hadrons simulated using the generic model
  • Flavor composition of 800 GeV anti-stop R-hadrons simulated using the generic model
  • Flavor composition of 800 GeV stop R-hadrons simulated using the Regge model
  • Flavor composition of 800 GeV anti-stop R-hadrons simulated using the Regge model
Reinterpretation material:
  • ETmiss trigger efficiency as function of true ETmiss
  • Single-muon trigger efficiency as function of |eta| and beta
  • Candidate reconstruction efficiency for ID+Calo selection
  • Candidate reconstruction efficiency for loose selection
  • Efficiency for a loose candidate to be promoted to a tight candidate
  • Resolution and average of reconstructed dE/dx mass for a given simulated mass for ID+calo candidates
  • Resolution and average of reconstructed ToF mass for a given simulated mass for ID+calo candidates
  • Resolution and average of reconstructed ToF mass for a given simulated mass for FullDet candidates

Pseudo-code snippets and example SLHA setups are available in the "Resources" linked on the left
column2: and more detailed reinterpretation material is available at http://atlas.web.cern.ch/Atlas/GROUPS/PHYSICS/PAPERS/SUSY-2016-32/hepdata_info.pdf.
